# Skillet Data Persistence

## AceDB Scopes

| Scope | Storage | Contents |
|-------|---------|----------|
| `profile` | `SkilletDB` | User preferences (vendor, tooltips, scale, transparency) |
| `server` | `SkilletDB` | Recipes, queues, notes — shared across chars on realm/faction |
| `char` | `SkilletDBPC` | Per-char tradeskill UI options, `include_alts` |

Never store recipe caches or queues under `char` — they belong in `server`.

## Queue Persistence

- Save after every queue mutation: `Skillet:SaveQueue(Skillet.db.server.queues, Skillet.currentTrade)`
- Load on trade change: `Skillet:LoadQueue(...)` then fire `SkilletStitch_Queue_Add`
- Queue entries must include `recipe` links (legacy entries without links are purged in `Upgrades.lua`)

## Schema Changes

Add migration steps to `Upgrades.lua` → `Skillet:UpgradeDataAndOptions()`, called from `OnEnable`. Pattern:

1. Detect old key/layout
2. Move or transform data
3. Nil out deprecated keys
4. Default new options with explicit nil-check (see `show_bank_alt_counts` pattern)

Do not rename SavedVariables root keys (`SkilletDB`, `SkilletDBPC`) or AceDB registration names.

## Stitch Link Storage

Recipe/reagent links are squished for storage (`squishlink` / `unsquishlink` in `SkilletStitch-1.1.lua`). Preserve this format when touching cache serialization.

## Notes Keys

Item notes keyed by full item link string under `SkilletDB.server.notes[playerName]`. Keep key format consistent when adding note features.
